        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32962",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What encoding have you specified for your Zend_View instance? By default, ISO-8859-1 is used, which would account for the stripping of Japanese characters. If you set the encoding to UTF-8, it should work fine.\n\nYou can do that in several ways.\n\nFirst, if you instantiate Zend_View yourself, you can pass the encoding as an option:\n{code}\n$view = new Zend_View(array('encoding' => 'UTF-8'));\n{code}\n\nIf you let ZF instantiate Zend_View (via the ViewRenderer, for instance), you can set the encoding manually at any time:\n{code}\n$view->setEncoding('UTF-8');\n{code}\n\nIf you are using Zend_Application, and the View bootstrap resource, define the encoding option for your View resource in your configuration:\n{code}\nresources.view.encoding = \"UTF-8\"\n{code}\n\nThis may also be an OS-specific issue. I tried your example on a Linux machine, and the characters displayed fine both when using ISO-8859-1 and UTF-8 as encodings.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-27T04:47:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-27T04:47:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32964",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "encoding is already set to UTF-8 into View resource...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-27T05:38:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-27T05:38:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32965",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Which operating system, and which version of PHP, then? As noted, I did my testing on a linux machine, and tried with both PHP versions 5.2.10 and 5.3.0 -- same results with both ISO-8859-1 and UTF-8 encodings set on the view object.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-27T06:01:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-27T06:01:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38238",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Late, but i am back to the error.\r\n\r\nSeems the \r\n\r\n<?php echo $this->escape('\u0197\ufffd\u672c\u8a9e'); ?>\r\n\r\nworks as expected.\r\n\r\nThe problem is if passing the Japanese text to a legend:\r\n\r\n$form->setLegend($valueLang);\r\n\r\nThen it doesn't display anything...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T03:25:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T03:25:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38239",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Did more research on this.\r\n\r\nThe Zend_View_Helper_Fieldset is doing this:\r\n\r\n                $legend = '<legend>'\r\n                        . (($escape) ? $this->view->escape($legendString) : $legendString)\r\n                        . '<\/legend>' . PHP_EOL;\r\n\r\nSeems escaping ($this->view->escape($legendString)) is actually removing the Japanese text.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T03:57:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T03:57:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38240",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The view encoding is UTF-8.\r\n\r\nDev system (can't test now on production system) is WinXP\/Apache 2.2.11\/PHP 5.3.0\/ZF 1.10 (but the problem is on other ZF versions as well, as initially i tested on 1.7-1.8 or so).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avantis",
                        "name": "avantis",
                        "displayName": "Cristian Bichis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T04:23:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T04:23:24.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
